ng effect on the energy-trading market. The Houston energy powerhouse, with =
annualized revenue topping $150 billion and assets of more than $60 billion,=
 handles transactions representing roughly one-quarter of the nation's trade=
d-electricity and natural-gas volumes. In less than two years of operation, =
its EnronOnline trading platform has become a central marketplace for the en=
ergy business and already has handled more than $880 billion in transactions=
