ouldn't be reached for comment.=20
It remains to be seen how much Mr. Fastow's removal will assuage an increasi=
ngly restive investment community. The action came after the 4 p.m. market c=
lose and followed a day in which Enron's stock once again plunged. As of 4 p=
=2Em. in New York Stock Exchange composite trading, Enron shares were at $16=
=2E41, down $3.38, or 17%. It topped the Big Board's most active list at nea=
